  "title": "The Inquisitor Makes a House Call",
  "summary": "In a secure pharmaceutical lab beneath the Twin Suns Hospital on Caspar, the Caspian Presav and hospital chairman Crestian Tarasar receives the Imperial Inquisitor Axel, who arrives in full Imperium regalia to discuss the fallout from a prison break that freed the ancient Sith lord Malus, also known as Lorn Rhys, from the Oubliette. Over Ithorian brandy and Whyren's whiskey, the two allies weigh the precarious relationship between the Caspian Union and the Imperium under the increasingly absentee Darth Malign, and debate the danger should Malign fall and a vacuum open. They assess threats from Korolov and the mysterious benefactors behind Malus's escape, agree that the doctor Lynae must be kept from being drawn into Malus's schemes, and resolve to loop in Johanna te Danaan. Stressing absolute secrecy given corruption in the Moff Council, Axel prepares to investigate other hidden prison facilities while Crestian offers Union forces and the local insight of Fleet Captain Vega Sevenna before the Inquisitor departs.",
